      "bullets": [
        "Analyze arithmetic intensity using the Roofline model to determine if workloads are memory-bandwidth or compute-bound on GPUs like Nvidia A100s.",
        "Use kernel fusion via PyTorch Inductor or Triton to group memory-bound element-wise operations and minimize slow global memory access.",
        "Leverage Tensor Cores effectively by aligning matrix dimensions to multiples of 8 or 16 to maximize FLOPS on GPU architectures."
      ]
    },
